The '''Lesser Mark of Illumination''' was the symbol of those who joined the [[Chalactan Adepts/Legends|Chalactan Adepts]], one of the [[Mark of Illumination/Legends|Marks of Illumination]]. It was a small gold bead (identical in every other respect to the [[Greater Mark of Illumination]]) affixed between the individual's eyes. It represented the seeker. Along with the Greater Mark, it was the symbol of the Adepts. [[Depa Billaba/Legends|Depa Billaba]] had both marks on her forehead.

